# ğŸ“Š Descriptive Statistics & Hypothesis Testing

## ğŸ”¹ Overview
Descriptive Statistics and Hypothesis Testing are fundamental concepts in data analysis and statistics. Descriptive statistics summarize and describe the main features of a dataset, while hypothesis testing helps make data-driven decisions by testing assumptions about a population.

Both are essential for Data Analysts to interpret data correctly and support business decisions.

---

# ğŸ“ˆ Descriptive Statistics

## ğŸ”¹ Definition
Descriptive statistics are numerical and graphical methods used to summarize and organize data so it can be understood easily.

## ğŸ”¹ Why It Is Used
- To understand the distribution of data  
- To summarize large datasets  
- To identify patterns and trends  
- To detect outliers  
- To support further statistical analysis  

## ğŸ”¹ Measures of Central Tendency
These describe the center of the data:

- **Mean** â†’ Average value  
- **Median** â†’ Middle value  
- **Mode** â†’ Most frequent value  

## ğŸ”¹ Measures of Dispersion
These describe the spread of data:

- **Range** â†’ Difference between max and min  
- **Variance** â†’ Spread of data from mean  
- **Standard Deviation** â†’ Square root of variance  
- **Interquartile Range (IQR)** â†’ Spread of middle 50%  

## ğŸ”¹ Data Distribution
- Normal Distribution  
- Skewed Distribution (Positive / Negative)  

## ğŸ”¹ Common Visualization Methods
- Histogram  
- Box Plot  
- Bar Chart  
- Pie Chart  

Descriptive statistics help in understanding â€œwhat the data looks like.â€

